Source: darkice
Section: sound
Priority: optional
Maintainer: DarkIce Maintainers <maintainers@example.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), autoconf, automake, libtool, pkg-config, libogg-dev, libvorbis-dev, libflac-dev, libasound2-dev, libpulse-dev, libjack-dev, libsamplerate0-dev
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://github.com/longgangfan/darkice

Package: darkice
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, adduser
Recommends: icecast2
Description: Live audio streamer (Ogg Vorbis, Opus, FLAC, MP3) for Icecast/Shoutcast
 DarkIce captures audio from a sound card, encodes it into formats such as
 Ogg Vorbis, Opus, FLAC or MP3 and streams to Icecast or Shoutcast servers.
 This build enables Ogg Vorbis and FLAC support out of the box.
